      },
      "type": "term",
      "surface": {
        "jp": "補助記憶装置",
        "zh": "辅助存储器",
        "en": "Auxiliary Storage"
      },
      "definition": {
        "jp": "データを長期的に保存するための装置。主記憶装置と異なり電源を切ってもデータが消えない。OSやアプリケーションソフトウェア、各種データなどが保存される。代表例はハードディスクやSSD。",
        "zh": "用于长期保存数据的装置。与主存储器不同，即使关闭电源数据也不会消失。用于保存操作系统、应用软件以及各种数据。代表性示例为硬盘和固态硬盘（SSD）。",
        "en": "A device for storing data long-term. Unlike main memory, data is retained even when the power is turned off. It stores the OS, application software, and various types of data. Typical examples include hard disks and SSDs."
      },
      "kana_helper": null
    },
    {
      "id": "itpassport_r6::term::p401::2",
      "anchor": {
        "page": 401,
        "block_id": "page_401_block_2",
        "section_path": []
      },
      "type": "term",
      "surface": {
        "jp": "ハードディスク",
        "zh": "硬盘",
        "en": "Hard Disk"
      },
      "definition": {
        "jp": "円盤型の磁気ディスクを高速回転させてデータを保存する記憶装置。",
        "zh": "通过高速旋转圆盘形磁盘来保存数据的存储装置。",
        "en": "A storage device that stores data by spinning disc-shaped magnetic disks at high speed."
      },
      "kana_helper": {
        "surface": "ハードディスク",
        "reading": "hādo disuku",
        "zh_concept": "硬盘",
        "auto_backfill": false
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "itpassport_r6::term::p401::3",
      "anchor": {
        "page": 401,
        "block_id": "page_401_block_3",
        "section_path": []
      },
      "type": "term",
      "surface": {
        "jp": "SSD",
        "zh": "固态硬盘（SSD）",
        "en": "SSD (Solid State Drive)"
      },
      "definition": {
        "jp": "半導体メモリを使った記憶装置。可動部品がないため振動や衝撃に強く、ハードディスクよりも消費電力が少ない。",
        "zh": "使用半导体存储器的存储装置。由于没有可动部件，因此抗震抗冲击能力强，且功耗低于硬盘。",
        "en": "A storage device that uses semiconductor memory. Since it has no moving parts, it is resistant to vibration and shock, and consumes less power than a hard disk."
      },
      "kana_helper": null
    },
    {
      "id": "itpassport_r6::term::p401::4",
